reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I needed a small table for beside my recliner. It is just what I wanted and fits the small space perfectly. It was packaged well, all the parts were included. The instructions were very clear and I put it together quickly. I liked that it had 3 legs so it worked well with 2 legs on my rug and the 3rd on the tile. It’s very sturdy. The screw on foot pads can be loosened or tightened to ensure table is level and doesn’t rock

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I live in an RV and do not have a lot of room for furniture. This small table appealed me because of not only its size but versatility it was easy to put together. It looks perfect in the small space between the couch and the recliner. The three shelves make it easy to store more things in a smaller space, it is stable on the floor as well. I would recommend this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute side table!
reviews.reviewText: Very happy with this side table. I wanted something small-space friendly as I live in an apartment, but one that still had a large enough surface area to be functional for a phone, drink, remote, etc. I love this one as it is a perfect size, and it has two smaller shelves below for decor or maybe remotes, coasters, whatever you like. It is the perfect height for my recliner and the design is very wood like and fits in well with my other real wood furniture. It was super easy to assemble and although lightweight feels very sturdy and well built. And for the price you can’t beat it.
